COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Petitioner, v. ESTATE of H. C. STONE, Estate of W. L. Hodges, W. L. Hodges, Trustee, H. C. Chenoworth, M. H. Graham, and G. H. Moore, Respondents. No. 7078. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 6, 1933. Dempsey & Mackay and Howard W. Reynolds, all of Los Angeles, Cal., for respondents.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and MACK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for respondents, ordered petition to review herein dismissed for failure of petitioner to file record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
